Classification problem¶

About the dataset¶

This dataset represents a set of possible advertisements on Internet pages. The features encode the geometry of the image (if available) as well as phrases occuring in the URL, the image's URL and alt text, the anchor text, and words occuring near the anchor text.

Objective¶

The task is to predict whether an image is an advertisement ("ad") or not ("nonad").

Attribute Information:¶

(3 continous; others binary; this is the "STANDARD encoding" mentioned in the [Kushmerick, 99].)

One or more of the three continous features are missing in 28% of the instances; missing values should be interpreted as "unknown".

Relevant Papers:¶

N. Kushmerick (1999). "Learning to remove Internet advertisements", 3rd Int Conf Autonomous Agents. Available at www.cs.ucd.ie/staff/nick/research/

Citation¶

@misc{Dua:2017 , author = "Dheeru, Dua and Karra Taniskidou, Efi", year = "2017", title = "{UCI} Machine Learning Repository", url = "http://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml", institution = "University of California, Irvine, School of Information and Computer Sciences" }

To see more about data documentation, visit:

https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/internet_ads/ad.DOCUMENTATION

Get data from the url:

https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/internet_ads/

First three features are height,width and aratio which are continuous variables.

Rest are binary variables. Out of which,

  • 457 features are from url terms
  • 495 features are from origurl terms
  • 472 features from ancurl terms
  • 111 features from alt terms
  • 19 features are from caption terms

Target variable is the last variable in the dataset.

# Check whether a given value is a missing value, if yes change it to NaN
def toNum(cell):
    try:
        return np.float(cell)
    except:
        return np.nan
    
# Apply missing value check to a column / Pandas series
def seriestoNum(series):
    return series.apply(toNum)

Missing value Treatment¶

In [15]:
# Printing total numbers and percentage of missing data
def missing_val(df):
    # Total Number of missing vales
    print("Total Number of missing vales:", df.isnull().sum().sum())
    print("*"*20)
    
    # Number of missing vales
    number  = df.isnull().sum()
    print("Number of missing vales in each column")
    print(number[number >1])
    print("*"*20)

    # percent of missing vales
    percentages = round(df.isnull().sum() * 100/ len(df),3)
    print("percentage of missing vales in each column")
    print(percentages[percentages>0])
    print("*"*20)
    return

def replace_missing_val(df):
    # Replacing missing vales
    df.iloc[:,0:3]=df.iloc[:,0:3].fillna(df.iloc[:,0:3].dropna().median())

    df['local']=df['local'].fillna(df['local'].dropna().mode()[0])
    #Recheck for confirmation
    number  = df.isnull().sum()
    print(number[number >1])
    return

    plt.legend()

    sqrt(df[i].var())
    #50th percentile i.e median(q2)
    q2 = df[i].quantile(0.5)
    #75th percentile
    q3 = df[i].quantile(0.75)
    #25th percentile
    q1 = df[i].quantile(0.25)
    #interquartile range
    IQR = q3  - q1
    #skewness
    print("skew:",df[i].skew())
    #kutosis
    print("kurt:",df[i].kurt())

    #convert pandas DataFrame object to numpy array and sort
    h = np.asarray(df[i])
    h = sorted(h)
 
    #use the scipy stats module to fit a normal distirbution with same mean and standard deviation
    fit = stats.norm.pdf(h, np.mean(h), np.std(h)) 
 
    #plot both series on the histogram
    plt.plot(h,fit,'-',linewidth = 2,label="Normal distribution with same mean and var")
    plt.hist(h,normed=True,bins = 100,label="Actual distribution") 
    plt.xlabel(i)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    print('*'*30)

Outlier Treatment¶

In [25]:
def outlier_treat(df):
    
    for i in range(len(feature_names)):
        figure = plt.figure()
        ax = sns.boxplot(x=feature_names[i], data=df)
    
    # The diamond shaped dots outside the boxplot indicates the outliers 
    for i in feature_names:
        q75, q25 = np.percentile(df[i], [75 ,25])
        
        #Calculate IQR
        iqr = q75 - q25
        
        #Calculate inner and outer fence
        minimum = q25 - (iqr*1.5)
        maximum = q75 + (iqr*1.5)

        #Replace with NA
        df.loc[df[i] < minimum,:i] = np.nan
        df.loc[df[i] > maximum,:i] = np.nan
    return

def predict(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train, y_train)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test, y_test)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ', cv)
    
    result_train.append(round((clf.score(X_train, y_train)*100), 3))
    result_test.append(round((clf.score(X_test, y_test)*100), 3))
    result_f1.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

In [56]:
def predict_pca(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_pca)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_pca, y_train_pca)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_pca)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_pca, y_test_pca)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_pca, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_pca, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_pca, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_pca, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_pca, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_pca, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_pca, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_pca)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_pca,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_pca, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_pca,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X_pca, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ', cv)
    
    result_train_pca.append(round((clf.score(X_train_pca, y_train_pca)*100), 3))
    result_test_pca.append(round((clf.score(X_test_pca, y_test_pca)*100), 3))
    result_f1_pca.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_pca.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_pca,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_pca.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

In [91]:
def predict_ffs(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_ffs, y_train_ffs)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_ffs, y_train_ffs)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_ffs)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_ffs, y_test_ffs)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_ffs, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_ffs, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_ffs, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_ffs, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_ffs, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_ffs, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_ffs, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_ffs)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_ffs,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_ffs, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_ffs,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ',cv )
    
    result_train_ffs.append(round((clf.score(X_train_ffs, y_train_ffs)*100), 3))
    result_test_ffs.append(round((clf.score(X_test_ffs, y_test_ffs)*100), 3))
    result_f1_ffs.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_ffs.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_ffs,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_ffs.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

In [108]:
def predict_up(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_up, y_train_up)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_up, y_train_up)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_up)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_up, y_test_up)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_up, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_up, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_up, y_pred,target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_up, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_up, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_up, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_up, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_up)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_up,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_up, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_up,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ',cv )
    
    result_train_up.append(round((clf.score(X_train_up, y_train_up)*100), 3))
    result_test_up.append(round((clf.score(X_test_up, y_test_up)*100), 3))
    result_f1_up.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_up.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_up,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_up.append(round((cv*100), 3))
    return

def predict_down(clf):
    print(clf)
    print()
    clf.fit(X_train_down, y_train_down)
    print('Accuracy on train set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_train_down, y_train_down)))
    print()
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_down)
    print('Accuracy on test set: {:.3f}'.format(clf.score(X_test_down, y_test_down)))
    print()
    print('Logarithmic Loss \n', log_loss(y_test_down, y_pred, eps=1e-15, normalize=True, sample_weight=None, labels=None))
    print()
    print('Confusion Matrix \n', confusion_matrix(y_test_down, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Classification Report \n', classification_report(y_test_down, y_pred, target_names=target_names))
    print()
    f1 = f1_score(y_test_down, y_pred, labels=None, pos_label=1, average='binary', sample_weight=None)
    print('F1 Score \n', f1)
    print()
    print('Matthews correlation coefficient \n', matthews_corrcoef(y_test_down, y_pred))
    print()
    print('Mean Absolute Error \n', mean_absolute_error(y_test_down, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average') )
    print()
    print('Mean Squared Error \n', mean_squared_error(y_test_down, y_pred, sample_weight=None, multioutput='uniform_average'))
    print()
    y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test_down)[:,1]
    print('Area under curve = %0.3f' % (roc_auc_score(y_test_down,y_pred_proba)*100),"%")
    print()
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test_down, y_pred_proba)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr,tpr, label='Area under curve = %0.3f' % roc_auc_score(y_test_down,y_pred_proba))
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()
    
    # 10-fold cross-validation
    #scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=5, scoring='accuracy')
    cv = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy').mean()
    print('Cross Validation Accuracy = ',cv )
    
    result_train_down.append(round((clf.score(X_train_down, y_train_down)*100), 3))
    result_test_down.append(round((clf.score(X_test_down, y_test_down)*100), 3))
    result_f1_down.append(round((f1*100), 3))
    result_auc_down.append(round((roc_auc_score(y_test_down,y_pred_proba)*100), 3))
    result_cv_down.append(round((cv*100), 3)) 
    return
